## Building on a Debian system:

 * apt-get install [live-helper](http://packages.qa.debian.org/l/live-helper.html) or rather use the latest from 'deb http://live.debian.net/debian/ ./'
 * `git clone git://git.debian.org/git/debian-live/config-webc.git`
 * webconverger/ is the base config file. Have a look around.
 * Take a look inside config/. You probably need to edit LIVE_MIRROR variables in the file bootstrap.
 * `lh build` in webconverger/ for [[maxi]] and mini/ for [[mini]]

Then typically use VMWARE for [[testing]] your freshly built image.

* [[todo]] has a list of bugs that need to be fixed. Please help me out and you will be [[acknowledged|acknowledgements]] for your contribution.
* Read [Testing setup guide](http://wiki.debian.org/DebianLive/Howto/Creating_a_Test_environment)
* Join the [Debian Live](http://debian-live.alioth.debian.org/) community. See the [dev mailing list archives](http://lists.alioth.debian.org/pipermail/debian-live-devel/)

## Debug mode with Webconverger

Debugging in Webconverger simply involves removing `nosudo` from the [[boot]] options.

